#: ../../S/scram-switch.rst:5
msgid "scram switch"
msgstr "scram switch"

#: ../../S/scram-switch.rst:7
msgid "n\\."
msgstr "名詞"

#: ../../S/scram-switch.rst:9
msgid ""
"[from the nuclear power industry] An emergency-power-off switch (see "
":ref:`Big-Red-Switch`\\), esp. one positioned to be easily hit by evacuating"
" personnel. In general, this is *not* something you :ref:`frob` lightly; "
"these often initiate expensive events (such as Halon dumps) and are "
"installed in a :ref:`dinosaur-pen` for use in case of electrical fire or in "
"case some luckless :ref:`field-servoid` should put 120 volts across himself "
"while :ref:`Easter-egging`\\. (See also :ref:`molly-guard`\\, "
":ref:`TMRC`\\.)"
msgstr ""
"[原子力産業から] 緊急電源切断スイッチ(\\ :ref:`Big-Red-Switch`\\ "
"を参照)。とくに、避難する職員が簡単に叩けるように配置されたもの。一般に、これは軽々しく\\ :ref:`frob`\\ "
"するものではない。これらはしばしば(ハロン放出のような)高くつく事態を引き起こし、電気火災の場合や、不運な\\ :ref:`field-"
"servoid`\\ が\\ :ref:`Easter-egging`\\ 中に自分に120ボルトをかけてしまった場合に備えて\\ "
":ref:`dinosaur-pen`\\ に設置される。(\\ :ref:`molly-guard`\\ 、\\ :ref:`TMRC`\\ "
"も参照。)"

#: ../../S/scram-switch.rst:14
msgid ""
"\"Scram\" was in origin a backronym for \"Safety Cut Rope Axe Man\" coined "
"by Enrico Fermi himself. The story goes that in the earliest nuclear power "
"experiments the engineers recognized the possibility that the reactor "
"wouldn't behave exactly as predicted by their mathematical models. "
"Accordingly, they made sure that they had mechanisms in place that would "
"rapidly drop the control rods back into the reactor. One mechanism took the "
"form of ‘scram technicians’. These individuals stood next to the ropes or "
"cables that raised and lowered the control rods. Equipped with axes or "
"cable-cutters, these technicians stood ready for the (literal) ‘scram’ "
"command. If necessary, they would cut the cables, and gravity would "
"expeditiously return the control rods to the reactor, thereby averting yet "
"another kind of :ref:`core-dump`\\."
msgstr ""
"「Scram」は元々、Enrico Fermi自身が考案した「Safety Cut Rope Axe "
"Man(安全綱切断斧人)」のバクロニムだった。話によれば、最初期の原子力実験で、技術者たちは原子炉が数学モデルの予測どおりには正確に振る舞わない可能性を認識していた。そこで彼らは、制御棒を素早く原子炉に落とし戻す機構を確実に備えた。ひとつの機構は‘scram技術者’の形をとった。彼らは制御棒を上げ下げするロープやケーブルの脇に立った。斧やケーブルカッターを装備したこれらの技術者は、(文字どおりの)‘scram’の号令に備えて待機した。必要とあらば彼らはケーブルを切断し、重力がすみやかに制御棒を原子炉に戻し、こうしてまた別の種類の\\"
" :ref:`core-dump`\\ を回避するのだ。"

#: ../../S/scram-switch.rst:22
msgid ""
"Modern reactor control rods are held in place with claw-like devices, held "
"closed by current. SCRAM switches are circuit breakers that immediately open"
" the circuit to the rod arms, resulting in the rapid insertion and "
"subsequent bottoming of the control rods."
msgstr ""
"現代の原子炉の制御棒は、電流で閉じられた爪のような装置で固定されている。SCRAMスイッチは、棒のアームへの回路を直ちに開く遮断器であり、制御棒の急速な挿入とそれに続く着底をもたらす。"
